	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Read together, the numbers tell a quiet story: a wife often gives far more than she receives, and carries a love she keeps hoping will be returned in equal measure. The "mental load" is real and largely invisible — the constant background hum of remembering, planning, and anticipating that no one thanks her for. Add comparison, exhaustion, and the slow drift of marital loneliness, and many wives arrive at the same aching question: <em>am I cherished here, or only relied upon?</em></p><p>These are not signs of a failing wife or a faithless heart. They are the symptoms of a daughter pouring out without being filled — trying to draw love from a spouse who, however good, was never meant to be her source. There is a Father who sees every unnoticed thing she does, and who delights in her apart from anything she carries.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
