	aFatherHeading={`A Father for wives`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>The answer to a weary, unseen wife is not a better husband, a tidier schedule, or more discipline to "try harder" in marriage. It is not even a stronger devotional life as one more duty. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a holy Father for a beloved daughter who happens to be someone's wife.</p><p>You spend yourself loving, covering, and tending the people in your home. But you cannot give a love you are not receiving. Before you were a bride, before you took a vow, before anyone called you "wife," you were a daughter of God — and that is still the truest thing about you. The cherishing your heart aches for, your Father has already poured out: He rejoices over you, He calls you His delight, He sings over you with gladness.</p><p>So you wake up tomorrow not first to serve, and not first to earn anyone's affection — but to be <em>cherished</em> by your Father. Then you love your husband from the overflow, not the lack. A wife who knows she is her Father's delight loves freely, without desperation, because her deepest need is already met in Him.</p>`}
