		{ heading: `To be seen and cherished`, bodyHtml: `To the wife who feels invisible, your Father <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/zephaniah/3" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">rejoices over you with singing.</a> You are not merely needed — you are noticed, delighted in, and treasured.` },
		{ heading: `A new name: My Delight`, bodyHtml: `Where you feel forsaken or overlooked, your Father <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/isaiah/62" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">renames you “My Delight Is in Her.”</a> Your identity is not what you carry; it is whose you are.` },
		{ heading: `Rest for the heavy-laden`, bodyHtml: `To the one bearing the invisible mental load, Jesus says <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read/matthew/11" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">“come to me… and I will give you rest.”</a> You were never meant to hold it all alone.` },
