	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Charles Spurgeon, George MacDonald, and Andrew Murray (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>When our Father said, "Let there be light," there was light. His Word does what He sends it to do. The love He speaks over you — His delight, His rejoicing, His choosing of you — is not a wish; it is a Word that accomplishes what it says, in your marriage and in <em>you</em>.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What the Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"Beloved daughter, I see everything you carry that no one else notices — the thousand small acts of love, the worry you hold quietly, the longing to be cherished. I see it all, and I am not silent about you. I rejoice over you. I sing over you. You are My delight.</p><p>You do not have to earn your place in My heart by being everything to everyone. You were My daughter before you were anyone's wife, and you will be My daughter forever. Come to Me when you are weary and let Me fill you. Receive My love as a weight you can feel, not a duty you perform — and then love from the overflow. You are not forsaken. You are not overlooked. You are altogether lovely to Me, and I will never forget you. I am your Father, and you are Mine."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for wives`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for all wives — the ones who carry the unseen weight of a home, who love faithfully while longing to be cherished, who hold so much together so quietly. Let them hear Your whisper above the noise of everyone's needs and expectations. Let them encounter Your love — not as a duty they perform, but as a weight they feel — and experience Your delight over them, apart from how their marriage is going or how much they accomplish.</p><p>Give them grace to prioritize intimacy with You above their endless serving, and to receive their identity as Your daughters before they are anyone's wife. Father, let every wife know she is altogether lovely to You; heal the places where she feels unseen, comfort her loneliness, and fill her heart so full of Your love that she gives from overflow and never from an empty well.</p><p>I pray Your protection over them from the enemy, from temptation, from bitterness and comparison, and from despair. Let them know there is no condemnation in You. Let them know You, their Father, as their true inheritance and reward, for every other gift pales beside the gift of You. And may they wake up every single day under the pour of their heavenly Father's heart for them.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
