	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for wives who feel unseen or unloved?`, answer: `Zephaniah 3:17 (your Father rejoices over you with singing), Isaiah 62:4 (you shall be called "My Delight Is in Her"), Psalm 45:11 (you are altogether lovely to the King), Song of Solomon 2:10 (arise, my beautiful one), and Isaiah 49:15 (your Father will never forget you) speak directly to a wife who longs to be cherished. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say to a wife who feels lonely in her marriage?`, answer: `Scripture meets marital loneliness with a Father who never leaves. Matthew 11:28 invites the weary to come and rest, Romans 8:38-39 promises nothing can separate you from His love, and Isaiah 49:15 says even when you feel forgotten, your Father has not forgotten you. You cannot draw all your love from a spouse; in the Father's Heart Bible™ you can meet the Father whose love fills the place no marriage can fully reach.` },
		{ question: `How can a wife feel cherished when her husband falls short?`, answer: `By receiving the cherishing her heart was made for from her Father first. You cannot give — or demand — a love you have not first received. When a wife knows she is God's delight (Zephaniah 3:17, Isaiah 62:4), she loves her husband from a full heart instead of an empty, aching one. The Father's Heart Bible™ lets you read these passages free, with audio, and meet the Father who already calls you lovely.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free online Bible with audio for wives?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on any phone or computer and read or hear any book, perfect for a busy wife to soak in the Father's love while she folds laundry, drives, or rests.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for wives?`, answer: `It is the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so the God you read has a Father's face. For a wife, that reframes everything: you come to the text not as someone striving to be a better wife, but as a beloved daughter being cherished, so you can love your family from overflow rather than depletion.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about a wife's worth and beauty?`, answer: `Scripture locates a wife's worth not in performance or appearance but in a heart turned toward God. Proverbs 31:30 says beauty is fleeting, but a woman who reveres her Father shall be praised, and 1 Peter 3:4 calls the hidden, gentle heart "very precious" in His sight. The Father's Heart Bible™ lets you hear these as a Father's tender words over you, free with audio.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say when a wife is weary and worn out?`, answer: `Jesus speaks directly to her: "Come to me, all who labor and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest" (Matthew 11:28). The Father sees the invisible weight a wife carries and invites her to lay it down in His presence. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you can read that invitation free, with audio, and meet a Father who fills the weary rather than asking more of them.` },
	]}
	ctaBottomHeading={`Be cherished before you give`}
